    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "7c21d2e1_b831a5a3",
        "filename": "android/skin/qt/emulator-qt-window.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 898,
      "author": {
        "id": 1079748
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-03-21T21:34:41Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Currently, we\u0027re not doing anything on |cancel| beyond ensuring that the callbacks from EmulatorQtWindow are not called.\n\nIn the case of ApiInstaller, this worries me a little. If the user hit cancel, it was likely because she launched a HUGE install that was undead. If we dont really cancel the install, it\u0027ll block future attempts at installing. This will confuse the user.\n\nwdyt?\n\n\nAlso, shouldn\u0027t this also mInstallDialog.hide()?\nSince |cancel| doesn\u0027t really trigger a call to EmulatorQtWindow::installDone, currently hitting the cancel button will seem to have no effect to the user?",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 898,
        "startChar": 8,
        "endLine": 898,
        "endChar": 32
      },
      "revId": "9a195b08404b08344aabd43be9a7cfd98d78bb14",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "7c21d2e1_b32c2634",
        "filename": "android/skin/qt/emulator-qt-window.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 898,
      "author": {
        "id": 1079203
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-03-21T22:31:14Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "mInstallDialog gets hidden by pressing the cancel button in the first place, so we don\u0027t need to manually hide it.\n\nI think you and I spoke about this offline, and I agree - cancel will almost always be used to stop a huge install.\n\nThe only option I see is kill()-ing the launched process, but that involves using the output PID before the functions, so it\u0027s a coin toss.\n\nIsn\u0027t that out PID our ONLY handle to the process in anyway?",
      "parentUuid": "7c21d2e1_b831a5a3",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 898,
        "startChar": 8,
        "endLine": 898,
        "endChar": 32
      },
      "revId": "9a195b08404b08344aabd43be9a7cfd98d78bb14",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "7c21d2e1_cb3be27d",
        "filename": "android/skin/qt/emulator-qt-window.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 898,
      "author": {
        "id": 1079748
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-03-22T00:19:18Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Oh yeah, now I remember.\n\nDon\u0027t have a trivial answer here. We either have to change runCommand to allow cancellation somehow, or call runCommand in non-blocking mode and have a platform independent way of waiting on the process.\n\nLatter is preferable, but I don\u0027t want to require that for this CL.",
      "parentUuid": "7c21d2e1_b32c2634",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 898,
        "startChar": 8,
        "endLine": 898,
        "endChar": 32
      },
      "revId": "9a195b08404b08344aabd43be9a7cfd98d78bb14",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
    },
